Festive days are not everywhere Holidays
In Hungary, public holidays are strictly regulated by law, so that the practice of redistributing the working days around the holidays has now become established, but the coming year will give us less such days.
In the EU and in America, too, something else is understood by "celebratory holiday".
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between state holidays and days without work.
Labour-free days are mostly church holidays, or are related to significant historical events.
For example, we also celebrate New Year: Both the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year are days without work - the latter alone so that the New Year celebrations can rest.
Throughout the year we have a total of fourteen holidays.
The state holidays are the 15th of March, which commemorates the revolution of 1848, and the 23rd of October, the memorial day of the revolution of 1956.
On 20 August the state foundation, on 1 May the work is celebrated, on 1 and 2 November we remember our dead.
In addition, there are two holidays each at Easter, Pentecost, and Christmas.
Since our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, the practice of "workday postponement" has proven itself in cases where we would only work one day before or after the holiday.
The price of the extended weekends, however, is that we have to work very well on the Saturdays before, or go to school.
When this day, which falls before or after the holiday, is to be completed in the end, is determined for long years by the Minister of Labour in a separate regulation.
The legislation applies to all employers and employees, public employees and civil servants alike.
Only companies and institutions in which the operation is continued without interruption, i.e. also on public holidays, are excluded.
This year, the working order is only a little confused by the holidays at the end of the year: from 24 December, life in this country will formally stand still, since most take time compensation for the days between Christmas and New Year's Eve, or the holiday reserved for this purpose.
Next year there will be more holidays in the middle of the week, or the end of the week, so that there will be less redispancies on the working days than this year.
The calendar is first "turned upside down" around the day of work, so that people can stay at home for four days at a time.
Saturday, April 26th will be a working day so that Friday, May 2nd can be a day of rest.
The second re-disposition is related to the holiday on October 23rd: on Saturday, October 18th, you will have to work Friday, October 24th in advance.
The end of the year, however, will be completely marked by the holidays, after everything will lie and stop from December 24th, even if New Year's Eve falls on a Wednesday.
Six deterrent little things to annoy colleagues
E-mails that we forget to send, voice messages that we never receive - harmless lies that we no longer notice: they bring "color" into everyday life at work.
The only question is whether you get used to these little inconveniences, or if you better face the challenge and try to avoid them incomprehensible, for others annoying situations consciously.
Tips.
"Sorry, I forgot to tell you that someone from the marketing department called" - says a colleague.
That it missed a meeting?
At best, you regret it and try to make up for it by calling the marketing department and confessing in a repentant way that you would have forgotten to direct the message (this is the less common method).
Most of the time it's done with an apology.
Before you get involved in embarrassing excuses, you should consider how to prepare truly unpleasant moments for your colleagues and try to avoid these situations consciously.
Borrowing something that doesn't belong to you?
There's hardly anything more annoying than reaching for a document, office supplies, or the phone, but it's not there.
Yesterday the notebook was still on the desk - this morning it is gone?
Or is the lost ballpoint pen discovered on a colleague's desk?
Without asking, you should not borrow anything from your colleagues, because they are right to get upset when they find that something has gone away.
So, don't put any envelopes or post-it from the office in your pocket, because it could hit you yourself: no more there, if you really need it.
Talking about colleagues' private lives?
There is no effective means of stopping a gossip that has already been put into the world.
Who did what to who?
Where and why?
One should not tie the information (or conjectures) about the private life of the colleagues to the nose if possible!
And if someone opens up and tells us his innermost secret, we should not abuse that trust!
It is best to keep silent like a grave, instead of directing the present person, even if others know about the problems of the colleague.
Reported sick for no reason?
If you call the office to report sick with a painful headache, because you feel uncomfortable right now, or just want to rest, you should be aware of one thing: your own work, irreplaceable accomplishments, projects with fixed appointments must now be done by your colleagues instead of yourself.
So don't mess with colleagues!
If you already know the day before that you will not make it to the office the next day, or that something could come in between, which is why you have to stay at home, you should report it in time so that neither the colleagues nor the boss are unexpectedly confronted with the absence.
Summing up, giggles, phone calls
We are now in the middle of our work, but is suddenly disturbed by the loud giggle of our colleagues?
Inadvertently listening to a telephone conversation you shouldn't have heard?
One should not annoy colleagues with humming, singing, loud conversations (which one leads over their heads), trampling, constant scolding or nagging.
All of this can be very disturbing, even if they are not precisely in a task (writing, planning, organizing).
Is it always the others' fault?
If a project is not finished on time, you have to send an important letter or important messages forgotten, one should not look for the fault of one's own forgetfulness with others!
If possible, do not talk about the chaos in the office or the noisy colleagues!
The best way to admit your mistakes is to apologize if others were affected!
The question of how to make up for the mistake or make up for the missing is all too appropriate!
In the office - a feeling like home?
Training Pants and Slaps: Comfortable for home, but has nothing to lose in the office!
Not even then should you dress so casually if the workplace would actually allow it!
Just don't get too sloppy - you should respect your colleagues as well as yourself to the extent that you dress accordingly in the office - if desired, also pretty and elegant!
To make it all right - or how to become uninteresting for others
Stop and go traffic, the car in the middle of every morning traffic jam.
