600,000 drivers missed the deadline to exchange their old driving licence, which expires at the end of the year.
Today is the last day to apply for the exchange so that the authorities will be able to issue a new driving licence by the end of the year.
However, the ministry does not fear that after New Year, hundreds of thousands of drivers will go on the roads without a valid driving licence.
According to the authorities, mainly those who do not want to drive have not changed their driving licence.
