The city administration produces around 2000 customers every day.
You have to stand by for about half an hour.
In Prague, about 140000 drivers have not yet exchanged their driver's license.
The issue of a new driver's license lasts 20 days.
But it is possible to apply for the exhibition with a shortened period of five days.
In this case, however, the driver must add 500 crowns.
From January onwards, drivers who fail to make the mandatory exchange by the end of the year and leave without a valid driver's license will face a fine.
The evildoer pays a maximum of 2,000 kroner.
The police, however, can also use a reminder when it comes to transgression.
In the event of an infringement, the penalty may rise to 2500 kroner.
According to previous information, the municipality may also impose a penalty on those who do not drive at all.
It was said that he could face a penalty of as much as 30,000 kroner.
The ministry already called on the offices to exercise mildness and impose a maximum penalty of 1000 kroner.
According to the spokesman for the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka, no one is threatened with a thousand crown penalty.
The driving licence was a document in which everyone could decide whether he wanted to own it or not.
It is not an identity card that everyone, and that is a valid one, must have.
People who don't want to drive anymore should hand over their driver's license.
It is sufficient to take him to the appropriate municipal office or send him there by registered mail.
At the end of the year, driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 will be invalid.
However, drivers have to gradually exchange other types of driving licences.
People with driving licences from 1994 to 2000 still have three years to exchange.
The validity of driving licences issued between 2001 and 2004 expires in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka, this is about 2.6 million more driving licences.
