The Congress agrees with the MIFID directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
Parallel to the parliamentary drafting, which ended its session today with the Congressional decision in the Senate on the amendments to the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
