Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of drawing up the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear to one what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance policyholder.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract that stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding severance payment in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which is composed of several factors, including age, gender, the time of drawing up the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accidents, higher contributions will also be due.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to pay less contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the enterprises, they tend to fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
Insurance companies must take a number of points into account when drawing up the premium.
For this reason, the driver also has to study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
We now list at this point the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance policy in order to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
Under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and young driving licences.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out comprehensive insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a comprehensive with excess, so that the benefits of a comprehensive insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay part of the amount incurred by the damage itself.
The amount will be determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, main representative of Spain at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is up to you to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the respective insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the above rates.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depend on the company and its revenues.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can allow itself to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is best to opt for a comprehensive insurance with excess.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, either in the event of an accident or at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been dropped.
Nevertheless, it is advisable for a married customer who has no children to take out comprehensive insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person permits it.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to have the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contributions are also low.
In this case, the best option would be a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount of 300 euros). In the case that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which only begins for the third year of the vehicle.
They are more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power which allows them to pay a higher contribution, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only uses with a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it is important to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it involves high costs that require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
